      "message": "[Critical] Line 442: This fallback timer can clear a newer search. Each call sets selectFirst_ to true, so an older singleShot can fire after a later setFilterAndSelect() and exchange(false), then call setFilter({}) for the current query. It also treats any search taking more than 1s as failed. Tie the timeout to the specific filter value/generation, or remove the fallback. For example:\n```suggestion\n    const auto expectedFilter \u003d filterString;\n    QTimer::singleShot(1000, this, [this, expectedFilter]() {\n        if (filter() \u003d\u003d expectedFilter \u0026\u0026 selectFirst_.exchange(false))\n            setFilter({});\n    });\n```\nUse the actual current-filter accessor/member available in this class.",
